-- Ormat Industries Sells 12% Stake to Fimi Fund for $79 Million
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-03-16T07:16:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-16/ormat-industries-sells-12-stake-to-fimi-fund-for-79-million.html
Ormat Industries (ORMT)  Ltd., an Israeli
developer of geothermal power plants, said today it agreed to
sell a 12 percent stake to Fimi Opportunity Funds for about 297
million shekels ($79 million).  Ormat said it will sell Fimi around 13.7 million shares for
21.7 shekels a share, in a company statement today. After the
sale, Ormat and Fimi will each hold almost 22.5 percent. In
addition, the deal stipulates that Fimi may increase its holding
to 30.2 percent in Ormat in two years.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Todd White  at 
 twhite2@bloomberg.net  